Ask HN: Would you say $100k is the new threshold of middle class in 2023?
text:
A six figure salary isn't what it used to be. With continued inflation and rising costs of living, it would not be unreasonable to say that an annual gross income of $100,000 is the minimum to be middle class, in the United States*.

If it isn't already the case, it soon will be.

Do you agree?

Also, what would you say is the new 6 figures? 400-500k? 800k? 7 figures?

How do you take efficient notes?
text:
How do you take notes?

I cannot decide which way is the best one and what to choose: a Kanban board, sticky notes, pen & paper, or simple To-Do Lists?

Notion / Todoist / Trello / what to use...!

I save some content in Kanban Board, then I'm missing quick notes I can save with a simple to-do list app. Later I switch to Notion, but finally find it too advanced.

How do you take notes to make it simple and efficient?
